cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR. 

This paper is about evaluating dialogue systems using Next Utterance Classification (NUC), which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of automated dialogue systems built using state-of-the-art machine learning methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also investigates human performance on the NUC task, which relates to human-computer interaction and could place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category. Finally, the paper uses datasets and techniques from information retrieval, which could make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
